mmary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading and testing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the ClassLoader.loadClass and getDeclaredConstructor might require `--add-opens` for the native image. It seems the generated metadata includes Field Buffer.address, which is good. On a positive note, there’s no direct reflection in my tests. I’m also considering the potential test package name io_airlift, which sounds solid. Next steps involve writing the file, removing the placeholder, and editing the build. It’s got quite a bit to tackle!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_axIcUrLH1yydj00mE3R4fdQq|fc_0b9534823d32c12b016a02361225c8819dac66734657805547", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.airlift/slice/0.36/src/test/java/io_airlift/slice/JvmUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_airlift.slice;\n\nimport io.airlift.slice.Slice;\nimport io.airlift.slice.Slices;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JvmUtilsTest {\n    @Test\n    void wrappedBufferReadsAndWritesDirectBufferVisibleRegion() {\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(8);\n        for (int index = 0; index < buffer.capacity(); index++) {\n            buffer.put(index, (byte) (index + 1));\n        }\n        buffer.position(2);\n        buffer.limit(6);\n\n        Slice slice = Slices.wrappedBuffer(buffer);\n\n        assertThat(slice.length()).isEqualTo(4);\n        assertThat(slice.getBase()).isNull();\n        assertThat(slice.getAddress()).isPositive();\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(0)).isEqualTo((byte) 3);\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 6);\n\n        slice.setByte(1, 99);\n        assertThat(buffer.get(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 99);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void directSliceProducesByteBufferBackedBySameMemory() {\n        Slice slice = Slices.allocateDirect(5);\n        slice.setBytes(0, new byte[] {10, 11, 12, 13, 14});\n\n        ByteBuffer buffer = slice.toByteBuffer();\n\n        assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(buffer.remaining()).isEqualTo(5);\n        assertThat(buffer.get(2)).isEqualTo((byte) 12);\n\n        buffer.put(3, (byte) 42);\n        assertThat(slice.getByte(3)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1326, "output": 923, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28361, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778529801159, "responseId": "resp_0b9534823d32c12b016a02360aa0c0819dbe0c2fb4ade17cfa"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_axIcUrLH1yydj00mE3R4fdQq|fc_0b9534823d32c12b016a02361225c8819dac66734657805547", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1661 bytes to tests/src/io.airlift/slice/0.36/src/test/java/io_airlift/slice/JvmUtilsTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778529815111}]}
