irst loading for these classes might allow us to trigger the initializer multiple times. However, I need to be careful not to use reflection directly unless necessary, especially since JvmUtils is package-private. It seems there are limitations with dynamic reporting and test execution that I need to consider.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the active class with the same fully qualified name and line numbers but with altered bytecode. That feels unacceptable for direct dynamic class loading. Currently, Native Image does not support this, and I wonder if I can catch an `UnsupportedFeatureError`. However, fundamentally, this approach falls under dynamic class loading. There are rules allowing for open-ended dynamic loading patterns, but Native Image's limitations complicate this whole process. Catching that error might be tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PbrTMxJnFbBospuaDd4OpdPW|fc_0b9534823d32c12b016a023960be20819d8ddcaf1645ad3513", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/io.airlift/slice/index.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6031, "output": 1160, "cacheRead": 46592, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53783, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778530635991, "responseId": "resp_0b9534823d32c12b016a02394e5c98819da7e71e61fb261691"}}
